title: Cori Bush
added: '''CoriAnikaBush'''<ref>[https://npiprofile.com/npi/1528523958]</ref>isanAmerican politician, registered nurse, pastor, and activist from [[St. Louis]], [[Missouri]], who is the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] Representative-elect for {{ushr|MO|1}}.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=July 31, 2018 |title=Meet Cori Bush, the Ferguson Activist Vying to Be Missouri's First Black Congresswoman |work= |url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/gy3dvj/cori-bush-missouri-congress-lacy-clay |url-status=live |access-date=June 22, 2020 |archive-date=November 14, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114164126/https://www.vice.com/en/article/gy3dvj/cori-bush-missouri-congress-lacy-clay }}</ref> On August 4, 2020, she defeated 10-term incumbent [[Lacy Clay]] in the [[2020 United States House of Representatives elections in Missouri|2020 U.S. House of Representatives primary election]], advancing to the November general election in the solidly Democratic congressional district. Bush is the first African-American woman to serve in the U.S. House of Representatives from Missouri. She previously ran in the Democratic primary for the [[2018 United States House of Representatives elections in Missouri|2018 U.S. House of Representatives election]] for [[Missouri's 1st congressional district]] and the [[2016 United States Senate election in Missouri|2016 U.S. Senate election in Missouri]]. She was featured in the Netflix documentary ''[[Knock Down the House]]''.
